Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: We did expect that Mr. Bryce would have declined to have his plain English speech converted into pigeon.Maori [sic]; but sad to relate, even he has succumbed to the evil influences of his surroundings, and has produced in his letter to Wahanui a document that would have delighted the heart of Sir Donald McLean.
